article.headline: Auburn 86, Western Kentucky 64
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Marco Killingsworth scored 18 points and Ian Young hit 4 of 5 3-pointers to lead Auburn past Western Kentucky 86-64 Friday night. Young finished with 16 points and Brandon Robinson added 15 for the Tigers (2-0), who used a 12-1 run to take control midway through the second half. The Hilltoppers (0-1) were led by reserve Antonio Haynes, who scored 15 points on 3-of-7 shooting from 3-point range. Anthony Winchester and Mike Wells added 12 apiece. Auburn never trailed, but the Hilltoppers kept the game close, pulling to within one on a 3-pointer by Haynes with 13:36 to play. On Auburn's next possession, Killingsworth missed two layups, grabbing the rebound each time, before finally hitting one and getting fouled. He completed the three-point play, and the Tigers scored nine of the next 10 points to take a 59-47 lead. They maintained a double-digit lead the rest of the way. The Tigers held the Hilltoppers to 37.9 percent shooting and forced 22 turnovers. Robinson and Nathan Watson had four steals each for Auburn.
